At least five volunteers come early each class day to prepare the stations before the students arrive.
Students participate in a series of hands-on activities, especially collecting pond water to view under microscopes.
Discover the Flyway stations also feature active learning such as Migration Madness.
Volunteers help students learn how to use student sized binoculars. Daryl Zerger, a volunteer for at least 25 years maintains the boxes of binoculars every month.
After stations and a snack students board their bus to travel to the Wildlife Area, 1 mile east of the Headquarters, where they continue their day of discovery.
